    <p>
        For interactive use, you first launch a shell such as cmd.exe on Windows,
        or Bash on Linux or macOS, and then issue a command at the shell prompt.
        To automate repetitive tasks, you assemble the CLI commands into a shell
        script using the script syntax of your chosen shell, and then you execute the script.
        You can install the Testbrain CLI locally on Linux, Mac, or Windows computers.
        It can also be used from inside a Docker container.
    </p>

